Final Invariant

Pantheon is not a collection of ideas.

Pantheon is an architecture for transforming intent into validated, reusable, compounding capability.

Everything else is implementation.

One suggestion I’d make after this is to stop expanding horizontally for a while.

Instead, deepen one complete vertical slice:

* Constitution
* Operator Kernel
* Compiler
* Greenhouse
* Tensor Store
* Spider Graph
* One real-world case study (for example, Wild Hawg)

If that single slice works end to end, you’ll have something far more persuasive than a hundred additional concepts, because you’ll be able to demonstrate the architecture solving real problems and improving itself over time.